questionnaireAnswers.experience: Even though it gives a good feedback I feel like it's not helpful to improve, it is more helpful to listen to the recording and compare it to the original tune
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: Not really because for me auditory cues are more helpful than visual cues
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: For me I won't need a super small scale as the overall contour gives enough information

questionnaireAnswers.experience: I think its very useful to see the graphs to analyse, but it would also be nice to have a real time option, so i can see my pitch, tempo and dynamics as they occur. Also, having the graph overlay with the performance metrics of the reference audio would be very useful.
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: Yes. It gave visual representation of what i was doing, which helped with analysing my performance.
questionnaireAnswers.payment: A couple euros maybe. If it was part of a bigger platform or had more features, possibly more.
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: I didn’t find myself using them much, but rather focused on the curves as a whole. Sometimes the highlighted sections were due to silences/ a change in the phrase, so it wasnt always that relevant.

questionnaireAnswers.experience: The tool looks great but seems to have some problem with alignments between what I sang and what was supposed to be sang.
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: They were at times. But they also highlighted parts I think were not too problematic.

questionnaireAnswers.experience: I liked the colored part that told me when i was doing it right. I felt very focused and engaged in the practice when using the analyzer. It was a nice experience that could help musicians get better.
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: Yes, i focused more on nuances, the hardest one was tempo because i didnt know if i was rushing or not
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: Yes, it helped me a lot to see where i was getting it right

questionnaireAnswers.experience: The feedback tool was not in real-time so I could not make immediate corrections. It was not very easy to adjust my pitch after the analysis tool. The feedback tool was useful in understanding where I was correct and where I was off however the necessary adjustments to make were unclear to me.
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: I think the reference tool was helpful when I could see that I'm already accurate. However I didn't feel that it helped me make the necessary adjustments to increase my accuracy.
questionnaireAnswers.payment: I believe this service could be beneficial and cost effective for practicing singing compared to taking classes. However, this seems to be more valuable as a practice tool rather than a learning tool. I believe it's helpful for tracking accuracy however it doesn't provide insight on the users singing technique / flaws. In that case a professionals feedback is more valuable, and learning the right techniques will set a better foundation for the singer. If this tool was in real-time, I can see its value as a practice tool that is immediate. If the user interface / UX was refined and it was in a plugin / standalone format, I could consider paying as long as it's significantly cheaper than vocal coaching.
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: For pitch it was clear, I could see which notes I'm able to recreate and which notes I'm off. Dialing in the first note with the help of the analysis tool gave a greater chance to correctly recreate the following notes.

questionnaireAnswers.experience: I think it was good, I would consider using it in my own practice to be honest. Does it exist anywhere?
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: It's hard to say, I hope there's a control group that is just practicing and listening to their own audio, because I feel like the practice inherently helps
questionnaireAnswers.payment: At this point maybe like $5 one-time charge, but only because I make a lot. I'd be more willing if I see statistics or studies that prove its efficacy

questionnaireAnswers.experience: It was good! It definitely was better than just plain practice. I liked the highlighted regions where it detected potential inconsistencies.
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: Definitely. It allowed me to focus on parts that I didn't know that needed some work (specially through the highlights).
questionnaireAnswers.payment: Personally I wouldn't need it, as I don't sing or play an instrument with the end goal of nailing a specific audio. But I can see a how many people would need it, specially singers. If I were one I would probably pay around 10€ for the tool
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: Yes! For every modality it helped me see my weakest moments when replicating the source audio.

questionnaireAnswers.experience: I liked the pitch one the best because it was clear what was wrong although I wish it had flat or sharp written on it.  I was a bit confused with the tempo one because I didn’t see feedback.  The dynamics one was perfect.  I think the audio analyzer was overall helpful in improving my performance
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: It helped as it showed me problem areas so I could focus on that when repeating my audios
questionnaireAnswers.payment: If I were recording music I would definitely pay for it because I think it is very useful for improving but at the moment I don’t have a need for it
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: It was helpful for the pitch but not with the tempo section

questionnaireAnswers.experience: the best of the analyzer was improving my tempo
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: yesss to look closely to my mistakes
questionnaireAnswers.payment: I don’t think so, just because i’m not into music industry. but it’s a really nice tool for improving
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: yess to paid more attention  to those

questionnaireAnswers.experience: I thought it was useful for understanding my general pitch stability and accuracy and seeing the tempo curve, but I wasn't able to make much use of it for dynamics. I liked the interface and the way that specific error zones were highlighted.
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: Overall, yes. It was more useful in cases where I was already close to the target, but often I was too far from the target pitch/tempo/dynamics to make much use of the analysis. There may also have been technical issues with my microphone that prevented me from getting the best out of it.
questionnaireAnswers.payment: I'd be glad to pay for a real-time plugin, especially if I could sing along to a reference track or an instrumental and compare my vocal performance. Perhaps $30-50?
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: They were helpful for pitch correction as I could pick out specific notes and improve upon them. I didn't really understand how it was supposed to work for dynamics but that could've also been an issue with my mic.

questionnaireAnswers.experience: I think that the feedback is useful for engagement and increase the desire of improvement. It could be useful, at some point that you have the graphics and try to adjust to them in real time.
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: I think It can improve the performances as you can look in detail after the performace where are points of improvement.
questionnaireAnswers.payment: If my work implied singing, yes, but I would compare it first to other similar tools if exists. If singing is a hobby I would not pay for it.
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: The pitch-graphic was the clearest to understand for me, as it is easy to interpretate discrete musical notes, that levels of loudness or tempo.

questionnaireAnswers.experience: I liked the different aspects, tempo, pitch, dynamics. I think it would help me fine tune my performances.
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: It helped me pinpoint where my mistakes were.
questionnaireAnswers.payment: I would pay a maximum of 5$ a month.
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: Yes they were helpful for showing me where I need to focus.

questionnaireAnswers.experience:
The pitch feedback tool seemed clear to me, but it could have improved if it displayed the direction I was going wrong in, i.e. if I was high or low.
Dynamics tool seemed nice too, but I didn't make many mistakes there.
Tempo feedback tool didn't load for me, I had to go to next screen.
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: The pitch one pointed out some notes I was getting wrong, so I tried to fix them. I guess it was helpful in understanding what notes I was getting wrong.
questionnaireAnswers.payment: In case there was additional natural language feedback on how I could improve, this would be like a personal instructor and I can see myself paying for it.
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: Yes definitely. The pitch curve and dynamics curve were quite good choices for the plot.

questionnaireAnswers.experience: It was useful specially in the pitch and dynamics exercises. I think it was helpful to fix some errors in my performances but also I would appreciate more real-time feedback.
questionnaireAnswers.improvement: Yes, a little bit! It was useful to visually see where in the performance I was failing, then I would be able to keep it in mind and fix it.
questionnaireAnswers.highlights: They were, but sometimes I wouldn't see any highlighted area even though I still considered the performance not perfect at all.
